# Vercel Web Analytics Integration

Successfully integrated Vercel Web Analytics into the VidMarkUp React application.

## Changes Made

### Files Modified:
- **src/App.jsx** - Added Analytics component from @vercel/analytics/react
  - Imported `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component to the root render inside the Provider component
  - The Analytics component is now active across all routes in the application

- **package.json** - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
  - Added `@vercel/analytics` to dependencies

- **package-lock.json** - Updated lockfile with new dependency

## Implementation Details

Following the Vercel Web Analytics documentation for React applications, I:

1. **Installed the package**: Added `@vercel/analytics` using npm
2. **Integrated the component**: Imported and added the `<Analytics />` component in the main App.jsx file
3. **Placement**: The component is placed within the Provider wrapper but as a sibling to the RouterProvider, ensuring it tracks analytics across all routes
4. **Verification**: 
   - Build completed successfully (no errors)
   - Application structure preserved
   - All existing functionality maintained

## Usage

Once deployed to Vercel:
- Analytics will automatically track page views and visitor data
- Data will be viewable in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab
- The tracking script will be served from `/_vercel/insights/*` routes
- Route changes will be automatically tracked thanks to the React integration

## Notes

- The existing linting warnings/errors in the codebase (not related to this change) were left as-is
- The Analytics component works seamlessly with the existing React Router setup
- No additional configuration is required - the component works out of the box once deployed to Vercel
